.TH "nfp_cpp_area_acquire_nonblocking" 9 "nfp_cpp_area_acquire_nonblocking" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfp_cpp_area_acquire_nonblocking \- lock down a CPP area for access
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nfp_cpp_area_acquire_nonblocking
.BI "(struct nfp_cpp_area *area "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "area" 12
CPP area handle
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Locks down the CPP area for a potential long term activity.  Area
must always be locked down before being accessed.
.SH "NOTE"
Returns -EAGAIN is no area is available
.SH "RETURN"
0, or -ERRNO
